a) via the web panel
====================

- Open the openfire admin panel (http://localhost:9090)
- Go to the Plugins page
- Upload the osw-openfire-plugin.jar file
- If you check the info log (Server Manager -> Logs -> Info) you should see the message
  "OneSocialWeb plugin has been loaded"

b) via the command line
=======================

- Copy the osw-openfire-plugin.jar file to the plugin folder of openfire (typically /var/lib/openfire/plugins)
- Wait about a minute (the folder is polled at regular intervals)
- If you check the info log (tail /var/log/openfire/info.log) you should see the message
  "OneSocialWeb plugin has been loaded"



